* Accessory after the fact to felonies
* Aggravated assault
* Aiding and abetting (various felonies)
* Arson / malicious burning of property
* Assault
* Assault on a peace officer / assault on law enforcement
* Attempted murder
* Battery
* Bribery (where applicable/plausible during coverups or influence)
* Burglary (residential/commercial unlawful entry to steal)
* Conspiracy to commit murder
* Conspiracy to commit robbery
* Contempt/obstruction of justice (destroying or hiding evidence, misleading investigators)
* Criminal damage to property (vandalism, destruction)
* Criminal facilitation / aiding criminal enterprise
* Cyber/fraud offenses (fraudulent schemes, identity deception in heists)
* Driving under the influence (if applicable in pursuit/crash scenarios)
* Evasion of police / fleeing and eluding law enforcement
* Extortion / coercion / blackmail
* Forgery (plausible in certain scams or identity deception)
* Fraud (scams, con jobs, deceptive financial schemes)
* Gang affiliation / participation in organized criminal activity
* Hit-and-run (leaving the scene after collisions or assaults)
* Illegal possession of firearms
* Identity theft / false personation (use of aliases, disguises for heists)
* Impersonation of law enforcement (where used in missions/setups)
* Incitement / solicitation to commit violent crime
* Kidnapping / unlawful restraint / false imprisonment
* Liability for reckless endangerment (public shootouts, chase endangering bystanders)
* Mail / wire fraud (if electronic/financial deception involved in heist-style schemes)
* Money laundering (processing/cleaning proceeds from heists)
* Murder / Homicide (including premeditated / first-degree murder — e.g., Devin Weston in “Deathwish”) (GTA Wiki)
* Negligent homicide (if deaths occur through negligent acts)
* Obstruction of governmental administration (interfering with investigations)
* Perjury (plausible if lying under oath to cover actions)
* Possession of stolen property / receiving stolen property
* Possession with intent to distribute (controlled substances where applicable)
* Public nuisance / endangering public safety (mass shootouts, explosions)
* Racketeering / RICO-style charges (organized, ongoing criminal enterprise participation)
* Reckless driving / vehicular assault
* Reckless endangerment
* Resisting arrest / obstruction / interference with arrest
* Robbery (including armed robbery / aggravated robbery)
* Sabotage (deliberately disabling or destroying equipment/vital property)
* Stalking / invasion of privacy (pursuit, paparazzi/harassment missions)
* Tampering with physical evidence (altering crime scenes)
* Tax evasion (failure to report illegal income)
* Terroristic threats / terroristic acts (use of explosives or threats causing public fear)
* Theft (grand larceny / petty theft depending on value)
* Trespassing (entering property unlawfully)
* Unauthorized use of a vehicle (joyriding / taking without consent — separate from grand theft in some statutes)
* Use/possession of explosives / destructive devices
* Witness intimidation / witness tampering
* Wiretapping / illegal surveillance (where surveillance/eavesdropping is used in mission setups)
